properties.hgv:advice: The easiest way take a road train to or through cornmarket is to start approach from the A423 [has direct link to UN's E05] then use the A4144 to head north to join the A420 to the south end of the cornmarket St. Indicate left at lights at carfax
properties.hgv:advice_1: put on your running lights and aim for the middle of end of cornmarket street (lookout for fixed silver bolards.  crawl in a traffic jam speed at walking pace or clower and monitor pedestrian movements all around vehical. stop to one side of suface marked
properties.hgv:advice_2: carageway.  note some old parking bays are marked with small silver disks (impotant) the road is hollow beneath and taking weight beyond the marks risks damage to celler roofs and a risk of eventual cave-in too).  If you are very long pauseing in the
properties.hgv:advice_3: carrageway is fine.  Stop as if for delivary.  When leaving check for pedestrians and animals lose switch lights on or slow flash headlights or hazards to clear pedestains stationary  imediatly in front then edge forward slowly so people notice that you
properties.hgv:advice_4: moving again then slowly crawl through pedestains that have equal or greater priorty to you here. Traffic lights at the north end will clear cross traffic but pedestrians will cross regardless till they notice you begin to pull out so start slow and they
properties.hgv:advice_5: from your path.  If your very long go straight into Magdalen St. and then through the wide A4144 on which you can continue to the A40 or you could chose the A4165 to another part of the A40 to the east  of the other
